==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Silvan
<hw>Sil"van</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>silva</ets>,
less correctly <ets>sylva</ets>, a wood or grove, perh. akin to Gr.
<grk>"y`lh</grk>; cf. L. <ets>Silvanus</ets> Silvanus the god of woods:
cf. F. <ets>sylvain</ets> silvan. Cf. <er>Savage</er>.]</ety> <def>Of or
pertaining to woods; composed of woods or groves; woody.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>sylvan</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Betwixt two rows of rocks, a <qex>silvan</qex> scene⟦br⟧
Appears above, and groves forever green.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Silvan</ent>⟦br⟧

